      {
        "content": "Social media companies systematically infringe upon user privacy by collecting excessive personal data without transparent consent. They track user behavior across platforms and even offline, constructing detailed profiles for targeted advertising and other purposes. This practice not only invades personal privacy but also exposes users to risks such as data breaches and unauthorized surveillance. Furthermore, the lack of stringent regulations allows for manipulative data usage without accountability. To protect individual privacy rights, social media companies must be subjected to strict regulations that ensure transparent data practices and uphold the fundamental right to privacy in the digital age.",
